data.description: Behold the wonderment of 1237 Littlefield Dr, with it's classic architecture and warm inviting feel. Woven into the very fabric of this home is a little bit of Christmas magic as this home is currently owned by the renowned "Pasco Santa" and for the last 12 years it has transformed each holiday season into a vibrant winter wonderland.  Nestled in the serene Oak Ridge neighborhood, sprawled across a mature 1.05-acre lot, whispered stories of joy and family gatherings can almost be heard as you approach. As you drive through the rustic gates, you'll be taken with the swaying trees and lush landscape. The circular driveway leads right to the front door. There, our journey begins in the grand foyer, where the majestic curved oak staircase greets you, reminiscent of scenes from cherished novels. Imagine capturing precious moments here, against the backdrop of this architectural marvel. Venture forth into the primary suite, a sanctuary of tranquility, featuring lofty vaulted ceilings, a cozy reading nook next to a bay window, and an en-suite bathroom with a lavish soaking tub and a spacious walk-in shower. The heart of this home beats in the living area, where natural light dances through the towering windows, playing off the elegant beams and casting a warm glow over the fireplace. The adjoining dinette space, complete with a elegant built-in dry-bar sits off the wraparound kitchen which features plenty of cabinet storage and it's own little desk seating area.  Adjacent is a large formal dining room complete with elegant lighting, chair rail and double doors leading to the side yard. Ascend the grand staircase to the upper level, where the remaining two bedrooms offer a retreat of comfort and ease, accompanied by convenient attic storage. The property also features a two-car garage and is situated in a community that celebrates the leisurely charm of golf cart travel. Off the garage you will find a workshop, perfect for tinkering. Through the back doors you'll enter the screened patio with a chlorine pool and 12-seater spa, a private oasis surrounded by towering trees and thick bamboo - a haven for relaxation and entertainment. The tree coverage combined with dual HVACs - both new in the last 3 years - mean a low electric bill. The location of this property is prime: close to shopping, churches, hospital and with 5 golf courses all within a 10 minute drive and it's zoned for the desirable Mitchell High School. NO HOA means bring your boat, your camper, your work trucks etc. The home is on a well (no water bill here!) and features a water softener system. Not a flood zone, so flood insurance will not be required by a lender. This classic beauty is full of magic and charm and ready for it's new owner to love and cherish it the way past owners have. Set an appointment to see it today! ***Offering a 1% rate reduction for first 12 months at no cost when you use our preferred lender. Ask your agent for details.***
